So, Birdman didn't
feel some type of way

26:01.227 --> 26:02.695
when you went on
tour with Lil Wayne?

26:02.729 --> 26:04.530
(laughs)
Yeah, he did.

26:04.563 --> 26:07.533
I told him I got to go
where the checks clear.

26:07.566 --> 26:09.268
Mm-hmm, and right now,

26:09.301 --> 26:11.871
that Cash Money is just not
as liquid as that Young Money.

26:11.904 --> 26:13.539
Really?
(dog barking)

26:13.572 --> 26:15.908
Whoopty Woo, shut up!

26:15.942 --> 26:17.209
(barking continues)

26:17.243 --> 26:18.244
This damn dog.

26:20.179 --> 26:22.181
(glass shatters in distance)

26:25.652 --> 26:27.654
(whining)

26:30.489 --> 26:32.959
(quiet clattering)

26:36.763 --> 26:38.497
Get him.

26:40.633 --> 26:42.268
Drop it, bitch!

26:42.301 --> 26:44.136
Drop it!

26:44.170 --> 26:45.404
(grunting)
Open it up.

26:45.437 --> 26:46.639
Let me see what
you stealing!

26:46.673 --> 26:49.075
Who sent you?
Who sent you?

26:49.108 --> 26:50.810
Who sent you?!
Thirsty!

26:50.843 --> 26:52.478
Thirsty. (groaning)

26:52.511 --> 26:54.480
Lucious's slimy-ass lawyer.

26:54.513 --> 26:56.649
You was taking my
masters for Lucious?

26:56.683 --> 26:58.584
I should blow
your head off.

26:58.617 --> 27:00.319
Ooh, surveillance bugs.
What?!

27:00.352 --> 27:01.487
You want to call the cops?

27:01.520 --> 27:04.623
No! No. No cops.

27:07.159 --> 27:09.495
Get out of here.

27:10.663 --> 27:12.665
You better not
come back.

27:12.699 --> 27:15.802
Tell Lucious
to kiss my black ass!

27:16.803 --> 27:18.304
You packing?

27:18.337 --> 27:20.973
See you are, too.

27:21.007 --> 27:23.009
(laughs)

27:28.480 --> 27:30.482
(elevator bell dings)

27:34.320 --> 27:36.689
Oh, so you had a party,
you didn't invite me?

27:36.723 --> 27:38.290
I'm offended.

27:38.324 --> 27:40.559
I don't even know
why I let you up in here.

27:40.592 --> 27:42.528
Try not to slash
none of my artwork.

27:42.561 --> 27:44.196
HAKEEM:
Wake up.
(groans)

27:44.230 --> 27:45.898
ANDRE:
Will you two stop fighting?

27:45.932 --> 27:48.334
Wanted to talk to you
about Uncle Vernon.

27:48.367 --> 27:49.869
JAMAL:
So sick of talking about

27:49.902 --> 27:51.037
Uncle Vernon.

27:51.070 --> 27:52.204
What's there to talk about?

27:52.238 --> 27:53.973
He tried to sell out Dad,
it didn't work,

27:54.006 --> 27:55.474
and he took the easy way out.

27:55.507 --> 27:57.543
Whatever happened between him
and Dad doesn't negate the fact

27:57.576 --> 27:59.445
that he always wanted
what's best for us, Jamal.

28:01.680 --> 28:03.682
He taught me
that it was my responsibility,

28:03.716 --> 28:06.652
as the oldest,
to always look out for you guys,

28:06.685 --> 28:08.654
to protect you.

28:08.687 --> 28:11.190
Instead, I made sure you were
at each other's throats.

28:12.524 --> 28:15.762
I wanted Empire so bad that I...

28:15.795 --> 28:17.696
I was prepared to let you two
kill each other

28:17.730 --> 28:19.165
so I'd be the only one left.

28:19.198 --> 28:21.533
Come on, Dre.

28:21.567 --> 28:23.502
What you talking about?

28:23.535 --> 28:25.671
It wasn't Hakeem
that had you robbed

28:25.704 --> 28:27.106
at Ghetto Ass Studio, Jamal.

28:27.139 --> 28:28.307
I set that up.

28:31.911 --> 28:33.679
Wait. When Jamal
almost got shot?!

28:33.712 --> 28:35.547
I didn't think it would go
as far as it did, okay?

28:35.581 --> 28:37.183
But it did.
He could've got killed!

28:37.216 --> 28:39.218
I didn't think it would
got as far as it...

28:40.887 --> 28:43.622
It was wrong of me.
I was sick.

28:43.655 --> 28:45.224
I'm sorry.

28:45.257 --> 28:47.593
It's unreal.

28:47.626 --> 28:49.395
There's nothing I can do
to change the past.

28:49.428 --> 28:52.498
I can... I can just say
that I'm sorry.

28:55.734 --> 28:58.604
I'm getting baptized
this Sunday.

28:58.637 --> 29:01.440
And I'd appreciate it
if you both would come.

29:04.410 --> 29:06.245
(sighs)

29:08.280 --> 29:10.282
Guess we all
make mistakes, right?

29:11.784 --> 29:13.219
I'll come.

29:13.252 --> 29:14.921
Thanks, bro.

29:14.954 --> 29:16.322
I'm not gonna

29:16.355 --> 29:17.656
go get shaded by the pastor

29:17.689 --> 29:19.058
just 'cause I can't
pray away the gay.

29:19.091 --> 29:20.793
I don't know where he stands,
Jamal.

29:20.827 --> 29:22.328
You should ask, Dre.

29:22.361 --> 29:23.896
It's important.

29:23.930 --> 29:25.597
But you know where I stand.

29:25.631 --> 29:28.367
You'd be coming to support me,
man, not the church.

29:35.774 --> 29:38.911
I want to help
heal this family.

29:38.945 --> 29:40.646
I want us to be
whole again.

29:40.679 --> 29:42.982
I mean it with
all of my heart.

29:43.015 --> 29:45.818
Think about it.

29:45.852 --> 29:48.821
Yeah.

29:48.855 --> 29:50.422
Thank you.

29:50.456 --> 29:52.424
All right.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.460
Thanks, y'all.

29:57.196 --> 29:59.431
ANDRE: Thirsty sent
some guys to break into

29:59.465 --> 30:00.833
Lyon Dynasty.

30:00.867 --> 30:02.668
Thirsty does
whatever I tell him to do.

30:02.701 --> 30:04.270
Yeah, for your business,
not mine.

30:04.303 --> 30:06.172
And certainly not
our family affairs, right?

30:06.205 --> 30:08.174
This family is my business.

30:08.207 --> 30:10.776
What, Thirsty
too hood for you?

30:10.809 --> 30:12.845
Me? No.

30:12.879 --> 30:14.446
I remember it all, Dad.

30:14.480 --> 30:16.849
I could have been
in the streets if I wanted to.

30:16.883 --> 30:18.885
I chose not to.

30:22.989 --> 30:24.957
You're testing me.
That's obvious.

30:24.991 --> 30:27.693
I'm not testing you.
I'm just telling you,

30:27.726 --> 30:30.162
the only commandments
I want followed here are mine.

30:31.363 --> 30:33.599
Check your faith
at the door, son.

30:38.504 --> 30:40.206
I can't do it.

30:40.239 --> 30:43.675
My faith is who I am,
and it's not gonna change.

30:43.709 --> 30:45.978
Dad, I want to make
a confession to you.

30:46.012 --> 30:48.180
Why? What you do now?
When Cookie first

30:48.214 --> 30:50.149
got out of prison, I'm the one
that told her to blackmail you

30:50.182 --> 30:52.118
and produce Jamal.

30:54.386 --> 30:57.656
I knew she had somebody smart
in her corner.

30:57.689 --> 30:58.991
I want you to know

30:59.025 --> 31:00.993
that I'm fully committed
to you and Empire.

31:01.027 --> 31:02.428
I regret ever
jeopardizing this company

31:02.461 --> 31:03.829
for my own personal gain.

31:03.862 --> 31:05.331
Okay, good.
I forgive you.

31:05.364 --> 31:06.832
Can we get back
to work now?

31:06.865 --> 31:07.967
I'm not finished, Pop.

31:09.868 --> 31:13.672
When I was off my medication,
before I went into treatment,

31:13.705 --> 31:17.409
I felt hated and
rejected by you.

31:17.443 --> 31:20.546
I wanted to hurt
you so bad...

31:20.579 --> 31:23.249
that I went into
your studio,

31:23.282 --> 31:25.684
put a gun to my head,

31:25.717 --> 31:27.719
and I pulled the trigger.

31:30.756 --> 31:33.059
I wanted to die.

31:33.092 --> 31:34.961
Lord saved me.

31:36.963 --> 31:40.466
I know you don't believe
in this stuff, Pop,

31:40.499 --> 31:42.468
but you gave me life...

31:42.501 --> 31:45.371
and God gives me hope.

31:45.404 --> 31:49.575
Will you come to my
baptism this weekend?

31:49.608 --> 31:52.278
It would mean everything for
me to have you there, Pop.

31:52.311 --> 31:53.912
You're asking me to come

31:53.946 --> 31:57.716
and watch somebody
dunk you in tap water

31:57.749 --> 31:59.885
and pretend
that that's gonna make

31:59.918 --> 32:02.554
all your sins go away?

32:02.588 --> 32:04.590
There is no... God.

32:04.623 --> 32:05.992
There's...

32:06.025 --> 32:09.128
You just need to
man the hell up.

32:31.217 --> 32:32.818
HAKEEM:
Laura, hold up.

32:32.851 --> 32:35.121
You're stalking me now?

32:35.154 --> 32:36.588
You won't answer my calls.

32:36.622 --> 32:37.923
I have a train to catch.

32:37.956 --> 32:39.791
I'll make it fast.

32:42.361 --> 32:45.164
Look, I'm sorry. I didn't
mean to come on to you.

32:45.197 --> 32:46.765
Did I lead you on somehow?

32:46.798 --> 32:49.101
No, you didn't, but I just
never met a girl singer

32:49.135 --> 32:50.336
that didn't get
down like that.

32:50.369 --> 32:52.604
Well, I don't
get down like that.

32:52.638 --> 32:54.006
Okay, I get it,
and I respect

32:54.040 --> 32:55.607
that you're not
that type of girl.

32:55.641 --> 32:57.643
You forgive me?

32:57.676 --> 32:58.977
Don't you want to sing?

32:59.011 --> 33:01.780
All I ever wanted
to do was sing.

33:01.813 --> 33:05.717
Not for money or fame
or any of that.

33:05.751 --> 33:07.953
It's corny, but I like
making people happy.

33:07.986 --> 33:10.122
When I seen you in that
little bar in Brooklyn,

33:10.156 --> 33:12.624
I was in a bad headspace.

33:12.658 --> 33:15.461
But I want your voice
to touch the world.

33:15.494 --> 33:17.796
You know, plus, I'm on
my mogul swag now.

33:17.829 --> 33:21.533
And you're the real deal, and
I don't want to mess that up.

33:21.567 --> 33:24.203
I won't ever push up
on you ever again.

33:24.236 --> 33:26.004
I swear.

33:28.006 --> 33:31.310
Look, my driver will take
you wherever you're going.

33:31.343 --> 33:33.679
I'll catch a cab.

33:36.248 --> 33:38.250
(car door opens)

33:42.754 --> 33:44.756
Take her home.

33:52.364 --> 33:54.032
* I never know what's
really comin', I do ignore it *

33:54.066 --> 33:55.867
* If I'd-a known a few years
ago, I'd-a made a hit *

33:55.901 --> 33:58.036
* I probably would've
bought some clothes,
even brushed my hair *

33:58.070 --> 34:00.206
* I'd probably be the one
or maybe be the only *

34:00.239 --> 34:02.874
* Go... go get in my lane,
I swear, this hater's phony *

34:02.908 --> 34:05.377
* So I... so I ca...
so I ca... *

34:05.411 --> 34:07.713
Who are you talking about?
(sighs)

34:07.746 --> 34:10.082
You're talking about
your pops, right?
Yeah.

34:10.116 --> 34:11.850
He 'posed to be here.

34:11.883 --> 34:14.853
Every time I spit a 16 for him,
it put a smile on his face.

34:14.886 --> 34:18.224
He ain't here,
'cause he's a rotten bastard.

34:18.257 --> 34:19.558
Hell you gonna say that?

34:19.591 --> 34:20.859
'Cause it's the truth.

34:20.892 --> 34:22.528
I didn't come here for this.

34:22.561 --> 34:24.062
Doesn't mean he didn't love you.

34:24.096 --> 34:25.564
(sighs)

34:25.597 --> 34:28.300
A lot of fathers
don't know how to show love.

34:30.569 --> 34:33.539
Look, I knew your daddy.

34:33.572 --> 34:35.974
And he loved you so much

34:36.007 --> 34:38.744
that if you cut
off his right arm,

34:38.777 --> 34:43.081
he'd reach over and hug
you with his left one.

34:43.115 --> 34:46.051
That's what you
got to lay down.

34:46.084 --> 34:48.120
You got to stop
running from it,

34:48.154 --> 34:52.591
and you got to turn and
meet it face-to-face.

34:58.096 --> 35:00.566
*

35:00.599 --> 35:02.901
* Should've never left me,
oh, my *

35:02.934 --> 35:05.737
* Tell me why you had
to leave me, oh, why *

35:05.771 --> 35:08.440
* Why you had to go,
why you had to go *

35:08.474 --> 35:10.442
* Try'na keep a grip
on my sanity, right *

35:10.476 --> 35:12.110
* 'Cause they don't really know
what it cost *

35:12.144 --> 35:14.780
* For this life, the hurt, the
hunger, the time never right *

35:14.813 --> 35:17.149
* Thoughts of killing everything
in plain sight, your word *

35:17.183 --> 35:18.950
* Is your bond,
if I could say word to my moms *

35:18.984 --> 35:19.951
* You know what I'm on

35:19.985 --> 35:21.453
* But you was my world

35:21.487 --> 35:24.122
* Never did wrong in my eyes,
forever your girl *

35:24.156 --> 35:27.759
* Crazy, what you made me
indirectly, but you saved me *

35:27.793 --> 35:29.428
* From a lil' girl to a lady

35:29.461 --> 35:31.096
* Still a hustler
like you raised me *

35:31.129 --> 35:32.164
* God bless your soul

35:32.198 --> 35:33.499
* 'Cause you're gone now

35:33.532 --> 35:35.100
* All is forgiven
'cause I'm grown now *

35:35.133 --> 35:36.968
* Gotta make it out here
on my own now *

35:37.002 --> 35:38.970
* I pick the pen up
and put the guns down *

35:39.004 --> 35:40.972
* Every word spoken,
never when in vain *

35:41.006 --> 35:42.974
* Speak it to the world,
take away my pain *

35:43.008 --> 35:45.277
* They say you live once,
when you go it's a shame *

35:45.311 --> 35:46.945
* I guess
that I'm sayin' the same *

35:46.978 --> 35:48.514
* Should've never left me,
oh, my *

35:48.547 --> 35:51.483
* Tell me why you had
to leave me, oh, why... *

35:53.151 --> 35:54.453
I'm glad you're here, Ma.

35:54.486 --> 35:55.954
(chuckles)

35:55.987 --> 35:58.824
You know, when you
boys were babies,

35:58.857 --> 36:03.161
my mama wanted me
to get y'all baptized.

36:03.195 --> 36:05.964
Babies don't know what sin is.

36:05.997 --> 36:10.302
No, I think you should
choose the Lord,

36:10.336 --> 36:11.637
then get baptized.

36:11.670 --> 36:14.005
That way, it sticks.

36:14.039 --> 36:16.041
I'm gonna make it stick.

36:16.074 --> 36:17.175
Mm-hmm.

36:17.209 --> 36:19.177
I have to.

36:19.211 --> 36:21.179
I'm not a good person, Ma.

36:21.213 --> 36:23.882
Stop saying stuff
like that, stupid.

36:27.185 --> 36:30.556
I've done horrible things.

36:31.590 --> 36:33.592
So have I, Dre.

36:35.894 --> 36:38.029
But we are good people.

36:38.063 --> 36:42.234
You wouldn't be here trying to
make it right if you weren't.

36:42.268 --> 36:44.770
God knows your heart.

36:44.803 --> 36:46.705
Now, keep your mouth shut.

36:47.906 --> 36:49.708
I don't need to hear
about what you did,

36:49.741 --> 36:51.743
and neither does anybody else.

36:51.777 --> 36:54.746
You look good.
I'm proud of you.

36:54.780 --> 36:57.416
(playing "Amazing Grace")

37:06.057 --> 37:08.260
Hi. Thanks for coming.

37:08.294 --> 37:09.461
Of course.

37:11.563 --> 37:13.332
Thanks, brother.

37:16.234 --> 37:19.371
Great to have you.
Thank you.

37:19.405 --> 37:21.940
What's up, man? How you doing?
What's up, man?
You all right?

37:21.973 --> 37:24.610
I'm happy you could show up
for your brother.

37:24.643 --> 37:26.612
Actually, I'm surprised.

37:26.645 --> 37:29.114
I don't know why,
Ma. We're family.

37:29.147 --> 37:30.582
We show up and we
support each other.

37:30.616 --> 37:32.451
Even if we don't actually
believe in each other.

37:32.484 --> 37:34.720
I believe in you, Jamal.

37:34.753 --> 37:37.489
Always have,
always will.

37:37.523 --> 37:41.293
How are things going
with your father?

37:41.327 --> 37:43.261
He's taking me
to the next level.

37:43.295 --> 37:45.897
I'm working with Ne-Yo,
we're planning a tour.

37:45.931 --> 37:47.933
It's everything
I ever wanted.

37:47.966 --> 37:50.802
Uh, everything you
ever wanted.

37:50.836 --> 37:53.071
I'm happy for you.

37:53.104 --> 37:55.607
You ain't got to lie, Ma.
We're in the house of the Lord.

37:56.642 --> 37:58.910
So is he coming?

37:58.944 --> 38:00.746
Nah.

38:00.779 --> 38:02.748
It's probably
for the best.

38:02.781 --> 38:05.651
That devil walk in here, this
whole place might catch fire.

38:05.684 --> 38:07.819
(chuckling)

38:11.457 --> 38:13.459
*

38:54.265 --> 38:56.702
(people murmuring)

38:58.336 --> 39:00.305
Ooh.

39:00.338 --> 39:02.808
Mention the devil name,
and he will walk right in.

39:02.841 --> 39:04.943
God help us all.

39:08.179 --> 39:11.383
I'm Andre's father,
Lucious Lyon.

39:11.417 --> 39:12.718
Reverend L.C. Pryce.

39:12.751 --> 39:14.185
Grateful you could join us.

39:14.219 --> 39:16.154
Thank you.
Your son

39:16.187 --> 39:19.991
is an, um...
exceptional man.

39:20.025 --> 39:22.461
He never ceases to amaze me.

39:25.363 --> 39:27.499
ANDRE:
Thanks for coming, Pop.

39:27.533 --> 39:28.700
I love you.

39:28.734 --> 39:30.135
I know you do.

39:36.374 --> 39:38.910
Please.

39:38.944 --> 39:41.346
I think I seen some angels
running for cover.

39:41.379 --> 39:43.749
Ooh.
(chuckles)

39:43.782 --> 39:47.953
Oh, let me make space
in case lightning strikes.

39:49.054 --> 39:50.556
What happened, Dad?

39:50.589 --> 39:52.591
I thought you
couldn't make it.

39:52.624 --> 39:54.225
I was in the studio

39:54.259 --> 39:57.863
with Freda Gatz,
and her rhymes moved me.

39:57.896 --> 40:00.766
She reminded me of how...

40:00.799 --> 40:04.269
important my presence is
to you boys.

40:04.302 --> 40:05.937
I was the one
that provided for y'all

40:05.971 --> 40:07.539
while y'all mama was locked up.

40:07.573 --> 40:09.240
I made this family.

40:09.274 --> 40:10.576
This family

40:10.609 --> 40:13.378
that you spy on,
rob and beat down

40:13.411 --> 40:15.213
when you can't control us?

40:15.246 --> 40:16.214
Huh? Oh.

40:16.247 --> 40:17.382
I got something.

40:17.415 --> 40:20.819
Take this bug
and stick it up yours.

40:23.455 --> 40:25.423
I'm sorry, Cookie,

40:25.457 --> 40:26.892
are you under surveillance?
(chuckles)

40:26.925 --> 40:28.393
Sucks, don't it?

40:28.426 --> 40:30.261
Quit trying
to steal our tracks.

40:30.295 --> 40:33.932
Quit sending those
tired-ass thugs to harass us.

40:33.965 --> 40:36.434
And quit trying to turn us
against each other,

40:36.468 --> 40:38.436
turn us all into sinners
like you.

40:38.470 --> 40:40.939
Preach, Ma, preach.

40:47.145 --> 40:48.480
From the book of John,

40:48.514 --> 40:51.082
"When these things came..."

40:51.116 --> 40:52.784
(quietly): When it comes
to sinning, Cookie,

40:52.818 --> 40:54.786
you don't need
nobody's help.

40:54.820 --> 40:57.355
And for your
information,

40:57.388 --> 40:58.624
I don't ever, ever quit.

40:58.657 --> 40:59.591
Shh!

40:59.625 --> 41:01.760
PRYCE:
Andre Martin Lyon,

41:01.793 --> 41:04.129
you repented
and confessed your sins.

41:04.162 --> 41:07.265
Do you agree to turn
from your old ways

41:07.298 --> 41:09.768
and embrace Jesus Christ
as your Lord and Savior?

41:09.801 --> 41:11.537
ANDRE:
Yes, I do.

41:11.570 --> 41:15.173
PRYCE: Then upon the confession
of your faith, I baptize you

41:15.206 --> 41:17.142
in the name of the Father...

41:18.677 --> 41:20.445
You don't cuss at your mama!

41:20.478 --> 41:21.446
Get in that tub!

41:21.479 --> 41:22.981
Get in that water!

41:23.014 --> 41:25.116
Get in there! Go on!
No, Mama!

41:25.150 --> 41:26.451
I'm sorry!
Come on!

41:26.484 --> 41:28.319
DWIGHT:
I won't do it again! No!

41:28.353 --> 41:29.688
I'm sorry!

41:29.721 --> 41:31.256
